  "text": "Human cDNAs of PKR (double-stranded-RNA-activated protein kinase) and PKR-K296R (death mutant [Lys 296 → arginine]KPR) were cloned in the pEF6/Myc-His vector (Invitrogen) in-frame with C-terminal tags. These plasmids have been described elsewhere [CITATION_1] and were kindly provided by Dr Xavier Saelens (Molecular Signalling and Cell Death Unit of our Department).",
